<TITLE> Committee to examine Coca-Cola investment offer </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 18 (bdnews24.com)  The government will form a committee to examine an investment proposal of Coca-Cola. The cabinet committee on economic affairs decided to form the three-member body, with prime minister' adviser Mashiur Rahman as its head, in its meeting on Thursday, finance minister Abul Maal Abdul Muhith told reporters after the meeting. Coca-Cola made an investment proposal to Bangladesh in 2008 after scrapping its contract with Tabani Beverage, a Muktijoddha Kalyan Trust enterprise, which was sharing a bottling franchise with another Bangladeshi company to market soft drinks of the American company in Bangladesh. The minister said the government would consider three things  whether the freedom fighters, who used to get financial benefit from Tabani during its business with Coco-Cola, would again have such support from Coca-Cola, whether there is any legal dispute between the two entities, and what would be the share of the government in Cocal-Cola  before reaching a decision. Muhith said the government would sit with the beverage giant once the committee submits its repor
